page.title: 06Ecology continued
page.content: Stickbacks, eels, carp bream even brown trouta are to be found. If not caught amongst other types. Even Gudgeon, usually a river fish are in one large hammer pond. It is suggested they were introduced as live bait for pike and remainder released at end of day. A pair of swans nested in one hammer pond one year. Bird life varies a lot with large variety of habitants, water, heavily wooded areas, mature deciduous woodland conifer plantations, scrubb areas awaiting replanting and surrounding open farmland. A good cross section of birds, with summer visitors like the Cuckoo and winter visitors like Pochards Kestrels nest but hunt on farmland with rare Barn Owl. Attractive Mandarin ducks havebeen nesting on pond of late and gulls have been visiting too.
